Privacy Policy

Last updated: August 1, 2024

Reddit Narrator ("we", "us", or "our") operates the Reddit Narrator mobile application (the "App").

Information Collection and Use
We do not collect any personally identifiable information from users of our App. Our App is designed to allow users to upload videos to their Facebook accounts using the Facebook API. We do not store or use any personal information or user data.

Video Uploads
The primary functionality of our App is to enable users to upload videos to their Facebook accounts using the Facebook API. All interactions and data processing related to video uploads are managed directly through Facebook's secure API services. We do not access, store, or manage any video content or user data associated with these uploads.

Third-Party Services
Our App integrates with the Facebook API to provide its core functionality. For more information on how Facebook handles your data, please review Facebook's Privacy Policy: [Facebook Privacy Policy URL]

Security
We take reasonable measures to protect the App and its users. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy

